almond cookies
via http://allrecipes.com/recipe/almond-cookies-i/

1/2 cup butter, softened
1/2 cup white sugar
1 egg
1 1/4 cups all-purpose flour
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 cup ground almonds
2 teaspoons amaretto liqueur

Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).

In large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar.

Mix flour and salt.

One by one, beat in the egg, amaretto, and ground almonds.

Gradually mix in the flour until well blended.

Optional: roll in sugar

Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.

Bake 5 to 8 minutes in the preheated oven, or until cookies are lightly colored.
